                            <comment id="135362" author="emoly.liu" created="Mon, 7 Dec 2015 03:56:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;OK, Herbert, I will update the patch for meet your requirements.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="135325" author="hyeung" created="Sat, 5 Dec 2015 01:22:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Two additional requests related to the first:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1.  Please allow setting of petabyte quotas using P similar to G and T.&lt;br/&gt;
Eg.  lfs setquota -u &amp;lt;user&amp;gt; 1P 2P  10000000 15000000 /nobackupp8&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2.  If it is straightforward, please allow setting of non-integer quotas.  If I want to set 1.8P exactly, I have to calculate it manually using the next lower unit to get an approximation.&lt;br/&gt;
Eg.  lfs setquota -u &amp;lt;user&amp;gt; 1.8P 2P 10000000 15000000 /nobackupp8&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="135066" author="gerrit" created="Thu, 3 Dec 2015 06:45:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Emoly Liu (emoly.liu@intel.com) uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/17441&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/17441&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
